You know that Python and Django is the way forward for your client, but with a mountain of legacy PHP code, where do you start?

Ben spent the last 3 years working with a thriving charity organisation to migrate their large PHP system to Django. He'd like to share some survival strategies.

This talk covers:

 - explaining the transition to your client
 - first steps and initial experiments
 - running PHP and Django in parallel
 - why incremental migration beats the "big switch"
 - sharing databases and authentication
 - making the experience seamless for visitors and staff
 - strategies for converting the code</description><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">Ben Sturmfels</dc:creator><pubDate>Sat, 06 Jul 2013 00:00:00 -0500</pubDate><guid>http://www.pyvideo.org/video/2233/transitioning-from-php-to-django-on-the-sly</guid><enclosure url="http://s3.us.archive.org/ndvpyconau2013/Transitioning_from_PHP_to_Djan.mp4" length="None" type="video/mp4"></enclosure><media:group><media:content url="http://s3.us.archive.org/ndvpyconau2013/Transitioning_from_PHP_to_Djan.mp4" mime_type="video/mp4"></media:content><media:content url="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=wWlmpoSN34I" mime_type="video/flv"></media:content></media:group><media:thumbnail url="http://i1.ytimg.com/vi/wWlmpoSN34I/hqdefault.jpg"></media:thumbnail></item></channel></rss>